de.upb.t2t.control.gui

Interface UserFeedbackProvider

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    DbEditingUserFeedback
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EditDatabaseDialogue.FeedbackProvider, MainTranscriptionPane, SingleWordStage

    public interface UserFeedbackProvider
    This interface assures its implementing classes to provide basic functionality in terms of offering the user feedback about the status of an operation.
    Author:
    Michel May(michel-may@gmx.de)

    • Method Detail

      • generalFeedback

        void generalFeedback(FeedbackMode mode,
                     java.lang.String feedback)
        The most basic way of giving the user feedback by displaying the given String. To facilitate programming, information about an operation's success, failure, error state, etc. may directly be read from the first paramter. This also allows for visual representations, such as warning signs or similar iconic codings.
        Parameters:
        mode - indicates the nature of the feedback.
        feedback - a message that the user may receive.

      • progressFeedback

        void progressFeedback(double progress,
                      java.lang.String feedback)
        Presents the user with feedback about a pending process. The first parameter indicates the estimated percentage of completion.
        Parameters:
        progress - the estimated percentage of completion.
        feedback - a message that the user may receive.
